claim: Approximately 61%—about six in ten—of patients with proteinuria in the normal range have subnormal uric acid levels.
extra_info: proteinuria level within the normal range refers to `U-PRO` > 0 AND `U-PRO` < 30; uric acid level below the normal range refers to UA < = 6.5; calculation = MULTIPLY(DIVIDE(UA < = 6.5, `U-PRO` > 0 AND `U-PRO` < 30)，100)
reasoning: Among patients with proteinuria in the normal range (U-PRO > 0 AND U-PRO < 30), 503 out of 823 have subnormal uric acid levels (UA <= 6.5), which equals approximately 61.12%. The claim of 'approximately 61%' is consistent with this result.

sqlite3 "/Users/david/workspace/claude-code-claimdb/test_dbs/thrombosis_prediction.sqlite" "
SELECT 
  ROUND(CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / COUNT(*) * 100, 2) as percentage
FROM Laboratory
WHERE CAST(\"U-PRO\" AS REAL) > 0 AND CAST(\"U-PRO\" AS REAL) < 30;
"
